    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-01-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-01-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="278"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d278">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Squiers</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-01-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 14, 1905</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>House agrees Senate sanitation bill reported by telegram of December 17<note
                        n="a" xml:id="d278fna">Printed in <ref target="frus1904#pg_253">Foreign
                            Relations, 1904, p. 253</ref>.</note> and President approves to-day.
                    Secretary of Public Works Diaz goes to Santiago immediately to superintend work
                    of sanitation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Squiers.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
